cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.HC, cs.CY 

This paper is primarily focused on learning to rank, which is a subfield of information retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a bandit algorithm for safe exploration, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses user feedback and click data, which are relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper deals with online learning and optimization, which could fall under the category of control theory (cs.CY).
